The parameters of this program has three options:
python knn.py --dataset /path/to/data/filename.csv --k-val 2 --split 0.8

1. dataset path
This value could be set by the user and it must be a path to read the data file.
2. k value
This is the k value defined as the number of nearest neighbors which can be set by the user and must be an integer.
This value cannot be less than 1.
3. split value
This number is the percentage of training data of all the data points in the dataset and this value is a float.
The default of this value is 0.8 and this value cannot exceed 1.